{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc96a61b-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee","identifier":"/us/usc/t2/s274"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"274"},"text":"§ 274.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Staff; office equipment and supplies","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Legislative Counsel shall, subject to the approval of the President pro tempore of the Senate, employ and fix the compensation of such Assistant Counsel, clerks, and other employees, and purchase such furniture, office equipment, books, stationery, and other supplies, as may be necessary for the proper performance of the duties of the Office and as may be appropriated for by Congress.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc96a61c-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1919-02-24/ch18"},"text":"Feb. 24, 1919, ch. 18","children":[],"tail":", title XIII, § 1303(a), (d), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/40/1141"},"text":"40 Stat. 1141","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1924-06-02/ch234"},"text":"June 2, 1924, ch. 234","children":[],"tail":", title XI, § 1101, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/353"},"text":"43 Stat. 353","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1941-09-20/ch412"},"text":"Sept. 20, 1941, ch. 412","children":[],"tail":", title VI, § 602, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/55/726"},"text":"55 Stat. 726","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddc96a61d-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddc96a61e-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddc96a61f-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"As originally enacted, section also provided for legislative counsel of House of Representatives, subject to approval of Speaker, to employ and fix the compensation of assistant counsel, clerks, etc. In view of nonapplicability of section to Speaker, employee, etc., of the House of Representatives pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/510/s531"},"text":"section 531 of Pub. L. 91–510","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s281"},"text":"section 281 of this title","children":[],"tail":", section has been revised to limit applicability to authority of Legislative Counsel of the Senate. See section 282a et seq. of this title for provisions relating to appointment of staff, etc., for Office of Legislative Counsel of the House of Representatives."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"iddc96a620-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1941—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1941-09-20"},"text":"Sept. 20, 1941","children":[],"tail":", substituted “President pro tempore of the Senate” for “President of the Senate”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddc96a621-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a622-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Designation of Deputy Legislative Counsel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/57/tI/s6"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–57, title I, § 6","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-09-29"},"text":"Sept. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/412"},"text":"113 Stat. 412","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/106/57/tI/s6"},"text":"“The Legislative Counsel may, subject to the approval of the President pro tempore of the Senate, designate one of the Senior Counsels appointed under section 102 of the Legislative Branch Appropriation Act, 1979 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s274"},"text":"2 U.S.C. 274","children":[],"tail":" note; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/391"},"text":"Public Law 95–391","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/771"},"text":"92 Stat. 771","children":[],"tail":") as Deputy Legislative Counsel. The Deputy Legislative Counsel shall perform the functions of the Legislative Counsel during the absence or disability of the Legislative Counsel, or when the office is vacant.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a623-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Senior Counsel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/75"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–75","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1957-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1957","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/71/251"},"text":"71 Stat. 251","children":[],"tail":", provided in part that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/85/75"},"text":"“No more than three employees in the Office of the Legislative Counsel of the Senate may be designated as Senior Counsel, whose compensation shall be $15,500 gross per annum each.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a624-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Additional Senior Counsel","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/391/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–391, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/771"},"text":"92 Stat. 771","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/95/391/tI/s102"},"text":"“Effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1978","children":[],"tail":", the number of employees in the Office of the Legislative Counsel of the Senate who may be designated as, and receive the compensation of, a Senior Counsel is increased to five.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–248","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-12-30"},"text":"Dec. 30, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/804"},"text":"77 Stat. 804","children":[],"tail":", provided in part: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/88/248"},"text":"“That effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1963","children":[],"tail":", one additional employee in the Office of the Legislative Counsel of the Senate may be designated as Senior Counsel, and the compensation of the additional employee so designated shall be equal to the gross per annum rate presently authorized for other employees so designated.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a625-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Increases in Compensation of Four Senior Counsels","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/59/tI/s105"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–59, title I, § 105","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-07-25"},"text":"July 25, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/89/275"},"text":"89 Stat. 275","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1975","children":[],"tail":", which provided in part that the four Senior Counsels in the Office of the Legislative Counsel of the Senate shall each be paid at an annual rate of compensation of $39,000, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/94/dE/tII/s212/a/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–94, div. E, title II, § 212(a)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2019-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2019","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/133/2775"},"text":"133 Stat. 2775","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/371/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–371, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/429"},"text":"88 Stat. 429","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-07-01"},"text":"July 1, 1974","children":[],"tail":", provided in part that the four Senior Counsels in the Office of the Legislative Counsel of the Senate shall each be paid at an annual rate of compensation of $37,620."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a626-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"1974 ","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"Adjustment in Compensation Not To Supersede Adjustments in Compensation or Limitations by President Pro Tempore of the Senate","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Adjustment in compensation by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/371"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–371","children":[],"tail":" not to supersede order of President pro tempore of the Senate authorizing higher rate of compensation or any authority of the President pro tempore to adjust rates of compensation or limitations under section 4 of the Federal Pay Comparability Act of 1970, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/371/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 93–371","children":[],"tail":", set out in part as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s273"},"text":"section 273 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddc96a627-3a6e-11f1-a0f3-db3efcbbb4ee"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Increases in Compensation","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Increases in compensation for officers and employees of the Senate under authority of the Federal Pay Comparability Act of 1970 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/656"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–656","children":[],"tail":"), see Salary Directives of the President pro tempore of the Senate, set out as notes under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t2/s4571"},"text":"section 4571 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
